[09:38.79]	Did I forget that by the house of York
[09:41.66]	My father came untimely to his death?
[09:44.40]	Did I let pass the abuse done to my niece?
[09:47.46]	Did I impale him with the regal crown?
[09:50.26]	Did I put Henry from his native right?
[09:53.06]	And am I guerdon'd at the last with shame?
[09:56.12]	Shame on himself! for my desert is honour:
[09:59.12]	And to repair my honour lost for him,
[10:01.86]	I here renounce him and return to Henry.
[10:04.79]	My noble queen, let former grudges pass,
