[11:53.04]WARWICK	Tell him from me that he hath done me wrong,
[11:56.23]	And therefore I'll uncrown him ere't be long.
[11:59.48]	There's thy reward: be gone.
[12:01.58]	[Exit Post]
[12:02.34]KING LEWIS XI	But, Warwick,
[12:03.49]	Thou and Oxford, with five thousand men,
[12:06.36]	Shall cross the seas, and bid false Edward battle;
[12:09.86]	And, as occasion serves, this noble queen
[12:12.79]	And prince shall follow with a fresh supply.
