[13:20.65]	But dreadful war shall answer his demand.
[13:23.64]	Had he none else to make a stale but me?
[13:26.58]	Then none but I shall turn his jest to sorrow.
[13:29.89]	I was the chief that raised him to the crown,
[13:33.14]	And I'll be chief to bring him down again:
[13:36.20]	Not that I pity Henry's misery,
[13:38.55]	But seek revenge on Edward's mockery.
[13:41.29]	[Exit]
